    <name>
      <text>9.2.19 (Find coefficient x^k)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find the coefficient of \( x^{@k@} \) in \(\displaystyle \left({@t1+t2@}\right)^{@n@}\).</p><p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>By the binomial theorem, the general term in the expansion of&nbsp;\(\displaystyle \left({@t1+t2@}\right)^{@n@}\) is</p><p>\[ \binom{{@n@}}{r}\left({@t1@}\right)^{{@n@}-r}\left({@t2@}\right)^{r} = \binom{{@n@}}{r}{@t1^(n-r)*t2^r@} \]</p><p>
We are looking for the coefficient of \( x^{@k@} \), so we need</p><p>\[\begin{align*} {@3*n-2*r@}&amp;={@k@} \\ r&amp;= {@j_val@}.\end{align*}\]</p><p>Therefore this gives us
the term in the expansion containing \(x^{@k@}\) as \[ \binom{@n@}{@j_val@}\times {@ev(t1^(n-r)*t2^r,r=j_val)@} = {@term@}. \]</p><p>The coefficient we need is {@ta@}.</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
